---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { ui } from '../../i18n/ui';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const t = ui[lang];
---

<Base
  lang={lang}
  title={t.nav_about}
  description="About Ihar Nestsiarenia — what I do and what I write about."
  alternates={{ ru: '/ru/about/', en: '/en/about/' }}
>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    I'm Ihar Nestsiarenia. Staff AI Engineer and Head of AI Baltics at EPAM (Lithuania, Latvia).
    I've spent more than ten years taking ML and AI projects from concept to production.
  </p>

  <p>
    My current focus is multi-agent systems, agentic coding, and quality in LLM applications
    (eval-driven CI, agent graphs, observability infrastructure). Alongside delivery, I run the
    AI engineering practice in the Baltics — hiring, mentoring, and programs for engineers.
  </p>

  <p>
    Here I write short notes about what I notice in AI work: not news, not surveys —
    observations that I myself find useful. Full work history lives on
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nesterione/" rel="me noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/nesterione" rel="me noopener">GitHub</a> — code and experiments</li>
    <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nesterione/" rel="me noopener">LinkedIn</a> — work history and the occasional thought</li>
    <li><a href="https://t.me/bayesian_noise" rel="me noopener">Telegram: bayesian_noise</a> — short notes; often the original source for posts here</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 14px;">
    Open to consulting and mentoring.
  </p>
</Base>
